OL,4,CGirl, 6, donates 'lifetime of hair' to
OL,5,Ccancer charity
OL,6, A six-year-old girl has raised hundreds
OL,7, of pounds for charity by having her
OL,8, "lifetime of hair" cut off.
OL,10,FAmelia Barratt, from Gloucestershire,
OL,11,Fdonated 10in (25cm) of her locks to the
OL,12,FLittle Princess Trust, which makes wigs
OL,13,Ffor children with cancer.
OL,15,FHer mum Jenna Barrett said Amelia had
OL,16,Fbeen growing her hair all her life and
OL,17,Fhad "never had a dramatic cut before".
OL,19,FThe schoolgirl also smashed her target
OL,20,Fof #550, the cost of making her hair
OL,21,Finto a wig, in just two days.
